      • test_join_simple

        public void test_join_simple()
                      throws InterruptedException,
                             ExecutionException
        Unit test for a simple join. There are two source solutions. Each binds the join variable (there is only one join variable, which is [x]). The access path is run once and visits two elements, yielding as-bound solutions. The hash map containing the buffered source solutions is probed and the as-bound solutions which join are written out.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException
        ExecutionException

      • test_join_simple_noJoinVars

        public void test_join_simple_noJoinVars()
                                 throws InterruptedException,
                                        ExecutionException
        Unit test for a simple join. There are two source solutions. Each binds the join variable (there is only one join variable, which is [x]). The access path is run once and visits two elements, yielding as-bound solutions. The hash map containing the buffered source solutions is probed and the as-bound solutions which join are written out.

        For this variant, there are no join variables. We should get exactly the same solutions but the join will do more work.

        Throws:
        InterruptedException
        ExecutionException
